Durban - A man was killed and another was left seriously injured on Friday morning after the truck they were travelling in rolled down an embankment off the N3 in Lions River, in KwaZulu-Natal. ER24 paramedics responded to the scene of the incident and found another emergency service already in attendance. “Upon closer inspection, paramedics found a large truck lying 30m metres down an embankment. Two men were found lying near the cab of the truck. Paramedics assessed the men and found that one man had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead,” Russel Meiring, ER24 spokesperson said. Meiring said the second man had suffered numerous injuries, was treated and medicated. “Once treated, the SAPS Search and Rescue raised the man to the awaiting ambulance utilizing various rescue equipment. The man was later transported to Life Hilton Hospital for further treatment,” he said. He said police were at the scene of the incident and were investigating. Police could not be reached by the time of publication. Daily News